  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled a relatively modest sum and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. While the breach of trust is significant due to the defendant's position as an accountant, a lengthy prison sentence is not warranted. A period of six months incarceration is sufficient to provide a punitive deterrent while allowing the defendant to remain in the workforce to continue making restitution payments.",
